    <body><div type="letter">
      <p>Friday 3 o'clock</p>
      <p>Dearest W. My cold is most severe; &amp; I think I must certainly put off the N's. But at any rate there will be no ungraciousness in doing so from such a cause. I am sadly disfigured now; the swelling not decreased; the eyes &amp; nose become frightful. I</p>
      <p>am however in good spirits. In fact my occupations leave me no time to dwell on my wretched sensations.--</p>
      <p>I am grieved at losing this delicious riding weather. Your drive must have been delightful.</p>
      <p>Annabella is very ill indeed; &amp; I can trust no one here. She must go to Town if not better soon.</p>
